Join us for the 62
nd
Annual Florida Seafood Festival on October 31 and November 1, 2025
Schedule of Events
Friday, November 1, 2024
10:00 am – Park Opens (No Admission Charge), Booths Open
4:45 pm – 7:00 pm – Christian Musical Entertainment
4:00 pm – Blessing of the Fleet
4:30 pm – Arrival of King Retsyo & Miss Florida Seafood
4:45 pm – Opening Ceremonies (Information Booth)
6:00 pm – Live Christian Music
7:30 pm – Live Christian Music Headliner
10:30 pm – Park Closes
Saturday, November 2, 2024
7:00 am – Registration for Redfish Run (Front Steps of Gibson Inn)
8:00 am – Start of Redfish Run
10:00 am – Gates Open ($5.00 admission, children under 12 free)
10:00 am – Parade Starts (Hwy 98)
1:00 – 5:00 pm – Blue Crab Races (at the top of each hour, children under 12)
1:00 pm – Oyster Shucking Contest
1:15 pm – Oyster Eating Contest
8:30 pm – Live Music Headliner – Mark Wills
10:30 pm – Park Closes

Florida Seafood Festival
Florida Seafood
The Florida Seafood Festival serves fresh Florida seafood!
Much thanks to the Franklin County Tourist Development Council, Florida Department of Agriculture and the Florida Restaurant & Lodging Association for their sponsorship of this annual event highlighting Florida Seafood.
Location
The Florida Seafood Festival is held annually
at Battery Park in downtown Apalachicola.

to see all accommodations in the area.

Board of Directors
The Florida Seafood Festival board of directors take time out of their busy schedules to organize and plan the festival each year which is a large undertaking. The Board is made up of all volunteers.
